    "body" : "<blockquote>\n  <p>I somehow found this to be neater than\n  using the StringBuilder/StringBuffer\n  approach.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>I guess it depends on what approach you took.  </p>\n\n<p>The AbstractCollection#toString() method simply iterates over all the elements and appends them to a StringBuilder.  So your method may be saving a few lines of code but at the cost of extra String manipulation.  Whether that tradeoff is a good one is up to you.</p>\n"
