    "answer_id" : 8700373,
    "question_id" : 523871,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p><a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/guava-libraries/\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Guava</a> is a pretty neat library from Google:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Joiner joiner = Joiner.on(\", \");\njoiner.join(sList);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3568624,
      "reputation" : 31,
      "user_id" : 2979550,
      "user_type" : "unregistered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/3e28f7b73cbec377936f85961ee5e241?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "user2979550",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2979550/user2979550"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1384180913,
    "creation_date" : 1384180913,
    "answer_id" : 19909010,
    "question_id" : 523871,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Next variation on Peter Lawrey's answer without initialization of a new string every loop turn</p>\n\n<pre><code>String concatList(List&lt;String&gt; sList, String separator)\n{\n    Iterator&lt;String&gt; iter = sList.iterator();\n    StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();\n\n    while (iter.hasNext())\n    {\n        sb.append(iter.next()).append( iter.hasNext() ? separator : \"\");\n    }\n    return sb.toString();\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
