      "post_id" : 37978678,
      "comment_id" : 70287404,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "FYI this implementation is O(n^2) as String::concat copies both strings onto a new buffer: <a href=\"http://grepcode.com/file/repository.grepcode.com/java/root/jdk/openjdk/6-b14/java/lang/String.java#String.concat%28java.lang.String%29\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">grepcode.com/file/repository.grepcode.com/java/root/jdk/open&zwnj;&#8203;jdk/&hellip;</a>"
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 8449580,
      "reputation" : 323,
      "user_id" : 6338857,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/3900dc5762cc4143b6b72342d7e468d9?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Sreekanth",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/6338857/sreekanth"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1484039228,
    "last_edit_date" : 1484039228,
    "creation_date" : 1466631337,
    "answer_id" : 37978678,
    "question_id" : 523871,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Rather than depending on <code>ArrayList.toString()</code> implementation, you could write a one-liner, if you are using java 8:</p>\n\n<pre><code>String result = sList.stream()\n                     .reduce(\"\", String::concat);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>If you prefer using <code>StringBuffer</code> instead of String since <code>String::concat</code> has a runtime of <code>O(n^2)</code>, you could convert every <code>String</code> to <code>StringBuffer</code> first.</p>\n\n<pre><code>StringBuffer result = sList.stream()\n                           .map(StringBuffer::new)\n                           .reduce(new StringBuffer(\"\"), StringBuffer::append);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
